## Setup Instructions

1. **Prerequisites**
   - A modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, or Edge)
   - A local web server (can use Live Server in VS Code)

2. **Installation**
   - Clone or download this repository to your local machine
   - If using VS Code:
     - Install the "Live Server" extension
     - Right-click on [index.html](cci:7://file:///d:/WEB%20DEVELOP%20PROJECTS/news-app%20localhost%20only%20new/news-app%20localhost%20only/index.html:0:0-0:0) and select "Open with Live Server"
   - Alternatively, you can use any local web server of your choice

3. **Running the Application**
   - The application will open in your default browser
   - You'll first see the landing page where you can log in
   - After authentication, you'll be redirected to the main news interface

## Usage

1. **Authentication**
   - Start at the landing page
   - Use the login functionality to access the main application

2. **Viewing News**
   - Click on category tabs (Cricket, India, Technology, etc.) to view specific news
   - Use the search bar to find news on specific topics
   - Filter news by time range using the dropdown menu

3. **Features**
   - Click the bookmark icon (📚) to save articles for later reading
   - Toggle between dark and light themes using the theme button (🌙)
   - Use the logout button to end your session

## Local Development

The application is designed to run locally without any backend dependencies. All data is stored in the browser's localStorage.

